nvert|220.5|m|abbr=on}}\n| 73 floors\n| 1976\n| \n|-\n| [[Atlanta Marriott Marquis]]<br>265 Peachtree Center Avenue NE\n| {{convert|169|m|abbr=on}}\n| 52 floors\n| 1985\n|\n|-\n| [[AmericasMart]]<br>Various Addresses\n| \n| Various Heights\n| 1961, 1979, 1992, 2008\n|\n|-\n| [[SunTrust Plaza]]<br>303 Peachtree Street NE\n| {{convert|265|m|abbr=on}}\n| 60 floors\n| 1992\n|\n|-\n| [[American Cancer Society Center]]<br>250 Williams Street NW\n| \n| 10 floors\n| 1989\n|}\n\n==Economy==\nThe [[U.S. Census Bureau]] has its Atlanta Regional Census Center in Suite 1000 in the Marquis Two Tower.<ref>\"[https://www.census.gov/roatl/www/ The Atlanta Region].\" [[U.S. Census Bureau]]. Retrieved on January 17, 2010.</ref>  Several additional U.S. Government agencies have their southeast regional offices located in the Harris Tower, including the Department of Transportation, Department of Labor, Small Business Administration, and Internal Revenue Service.\n\nThe [[Diplomatic missions of Argentina|Consulate-General of Argentina]] is located in Suite 2101 in the Marquis One Tower.<ref>\"[http://www.consuladoargentinoatlanta.org/contactenos.htm Cont\u00e1ctenos].\" [[Diplomatic missions of Argentina|Consulate-General of Argentina in Atlanta]]. Retrieved on July 28, 2009.</ref><ref>\"[http://www.peachtreecenter.com/pdfs/international_710.pdf Peachtree Center]{{dead link|date=January 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}\" (Map). Peachtree Center. Retrieved on July 28, 2009.</ref><!--Marquis One Tower = 254 Peachtree Center Avenue--> The [[Diplomatic missions of Germany|Consulate-General of Germany]] is located in Suite 901 of the Marquis Two Tower.<ref>\"[http://www.germany.info/Vertretung/usa/en/03__Consulates/Atlanta/01/__Data.html Address, Contact and Office Hours] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081118153747/http://www.germany.info/Vertretung/usa/en/03__Consulates/Atlanta/01/__Data.html |date=2008-11-18 }}.\" [[Diplomatic missions of Germany|Consulate